data.name: Marill

attacks.name: Squirt
attacks.text: Choose 1 of your opponent's Pokémon. This attack does 10 damage to that Pokémon. Don't apply Weakness and Resistance.

data.flavorText: This Pokémon's fur repels water like a duck's feathers, allowing it to stay dry and fluffy even in water.

data.name: Marill

attacks.name: Water Gun
attacks.text: Does 20 damage plus 10 more damage for each Energy attached to Marill but not used to pay for this attack's Energy cost. You can't add more than 20 damage in this way.

data.flavorText: The tip of its tail, which contains oil that is lighter than water, lets it swim without drowning.

data.name: Marill
data.flavorText: The oil-filled tail functions as a buoy, so it's fine even in rivers with strong currents.

data.name: Marill

attacks.name: Bubble
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

data.flavorText: The fur on its body naturally repels water. It can stay dry, even when it plays in the water.

data.name: Marill

attacks.name: Water Splash
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 10 damage plus 10 more damage.

data.flavorText: The end of its tail serves as a buoy that keeps it from drowning, even in a vicious current.

attacks.name: Minor Errand-Running
attacks.text: Search your deck for up to 2 basic Energy cards, show them to your opponent, and put them into your hand. Shuffle your deck afterward.

data.name: Marill

attacks.name: Defense Curl
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, prevent all damage done to Marill during your opponent's next turn. (Any other effects of attacks still happen.)

attacks.name: Bubble Bomb
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Paralyzed. If tails, Marill does 10 damage to itself.

data.flavorText: The end of its tail serves as a buoy that keeps it from drowning, even in a vicious current.

data.name: Marill
data.flavorText: The tip of its tail is filled with oil that is lighter than water, so it acts as a float.

attacks.name: Double Bubble
attacks.text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 10 damage times the number of heads. If either of the coins is heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

attacks.name: Jump On
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 10 damage plus 20 more damage.

attacks.name: Sleepy Ball
attacks.text: The Defending Pokémon is now Asleep.

data.name: Marill

attacks.name: Rollout
attacks.text: If Marill is evolved from Azurill, this attack does 10 damage plus 20 more damage.

attacks.name: Splashing Turn
attacks.text: Switch Marill with 1 of your Benched Pokémon.

data.flavorText: Using its tail as a float, it dives underwater. It likes eating plants that grow on river bottoms.
